<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-07-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-07-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="454" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d454">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Sleeper</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-07-21"><hi rend="italic">July 21,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(In reply to Department’s cablegram of the 20th, Mr. Sleeper says the
                            matter is fully reported in dispatch 135, mailed this day, and that the
                            alleged outrage is not apparent.)</p>
                    </div>
